Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Jakarta.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 0.1 percent to 4,224.00,
gaining for a fourth day to a record close.  PT Astra Agro Lestari (AALI)  ,  Indonesia â€™s biggest listed
plantation company by market value, rose 1.2 percent to 21,600
rupiah, the most since March 29. Astra Agro signed an agreement
for a loan of as much as $50 million with three foreign banks,
Finance Director Santosa said in Jakarta today.  PT Tambang Batubara Bukit Asam (PTBA)  , a state-owned
coal producer, climbed 0.8 percent to 18,300 rupiah. Bukit Asam
will pay a dividend of 700.1 rupiah a share, or a total of 1.85
trillion rupiah ($199 million) compared with 1.21 trillion
rupiah paid out last year, the company said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
